Notable motivational speaker, entrepreneur and life Coach, Engineer Abiodun Fijabi will on Tuesday, May 31, 2022, deliver the 7th matriculation lecture at the Chrisland University in Abeokuta, Ogun State. The general theme for the ceremony which holds at noon at the University Auditorium is: “Engaging Wisdom for Intellectual Radiance”. Fijabi, the Chief Executive Officer of Lord Princely Associates will, in particular, be delivering a paper titled: “Unleashing the Leadership Spirit in You: the ‘What’, the ‘Why’ and the ‘How’”? -Advertisement- With a mission to prepare young adults for a lifetime of leadership development and service, the guest lecturer is expected to motivate and inspire the fresh students as they are officially matriculated into the University. Fijabi who is also the Proprietor of the popular Abeokuta-based educational institution, Elyon College and Leadership Academy, is a graduate of the University of Lagos, Akoka. The Founder and Chancellor, Dr Winifred Awosika, an educator, an entrepreneur of repute and a pioneer of quality education across the country is expected at the formal enrolment of fresh boys and girls. The University’s Vice-Chancellor, Professor (Mrs.) Chinedum Peace Babalola is expected to chair the ceremony. Also expected at the ceremony is a seasoned academic and the Pro-Chancellor, Distinguished Professor Ayodeji Olukoju, a two-time former Vice-Chancellor of Caleb University and a Distinguished Professor of History at UNILAG.